===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰer-|id=bowels}}
From {{inh|en|enm|yarne}}, {{m|enm|ȝern}}, {{m|enm|yarn}}, from the {{inh|en|ang|ġearn||yarn, spun wool}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*garn}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*garną||yarn}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰorn-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*ǵʰer-||tharm, guts, intestines|id=bowels}}.
{{rel-top|Cognates}}
Akin to {{cog|fy|jern}}, {{cog|nl|garen||yarn}}, {{cog|de|Garn||yarn}}, {{cog|da|garn}}, {{cog|sv|garn||yarn, thread}}, {{cog|is|garn||yarn}}, {{cog|la|hernia||rupture}}, {{cog|grc|χορδή||string}}, {{cog|sa|हिर||band}}. Compare also the obsolete doublet {{l|en|garn}}. {{rel-bottom}}
